    <fullPolicyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "markup": "<p data-start=\"293\" data-end=\"563\"><strong data-start=\"293\" data-end=\"325\">Eligibility for Overtime Pay</strong><br data-start=\"325\" data-end=\"328\">Non-exempt employees are entitled to receive overtime pay for all hours worked beyond 40 hours in a standard workweek. Overtime will be paid at one and one-half times the employee’s regular hourly rate unless otherwise required by law.</p>\n<p data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"874\"><strong data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"593\">Pre-Approval Requirement</strong><br data-start=\"593\" data-end=\"596\">All overtime work must be pre-approved by your manager. Working overtime without prior approval may result in disciplinary action, even if the work was necessary or beneficial to the Company. Managers are responsible for ensuring that overtime is only authorized when necessary.</p>\n<p data-start=\"876\" data-end=\"1130\"><strong data-start=\"876\" data-end=\"898\">Recording Overtime</strong><br data-start=\"898\" data-end=\"901\">If you work overtime, it must be accurately recorded in the Company’s timekeeping system. Falsifying or failing to report time worked—whether regular or overtime hours—is strictly prohibited and may result in disciplinary action.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1132\" data-end=\"1420\"><strong data-start=\"1132\" data-end=\"1155\">Overtime Scheduling</strong><br data-start=\"1155\" data-end=\"1158\">The Company may require employees to work overtime to meet business needs. While we try to provide advance notice, there may be occasions where short notice is unavoidable. Refusing to work mandatory overtime without a valid reason may lead to corrective action.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1422\" data-end=\"1691\"><strong data-start=\"1422\" data-end=\"1459\">Comp Time (Compensatory Time Off)</strong><br data-start=\"1459\" data-end=\"1462\">We do not provide compensatory time off in place of overtime pay unless expressly required by law or authorized through a formal agreement. All earned overtime must be compensated in accordance with applicable wage and hour laws.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1693\" data-end=\"1857\"><strong data-start=\"1693\" data-end=\"1718\">Questions or Concerns</strong><br data-start=\"1718\" data-end=\"1721\">If you have any questions about your eligibility for overtime or how overtime is calculated, please contact your manager or the HR team.</p>",
