        "markup": "<p data-start=\"992\" data-end=\"1083\">California law requires overtime pay for non-exempt employees at 1.5× the regular rate for:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"1086\" data-end=\"1229\">\n<li data-start=\"1086\" data-end=\"1116\">\n<p data-start=\"1088\" data-end=\"1116\">Hours worked over 8 in a day</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1119\" data-end=\"1151\">\n<p data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1151\">Hours worked over 40 in a week</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1154\" data-end=\"1227\">\n<p data-start=\"1156\" data-end=\"1227\">The first 8 hours worked on the seventh consecutive day in a workweek</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1232\" data-end=\"1265\">Double time (2×) is required for:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"1268\" data-end=\"1358\">\n<li data-start=\"1268\" data-end=\"1292\">\n<p data-start=\"1270\" data-end=\"1292\">Hours over 12 in a day</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1295\" data-end=\"1356\">\n<p data-start=\"1297\" data-end=\"1356\">Hours over 8 on the seventh consecutive day in a workweek</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1361\" data-end=\"1493\">These provisions apply <strong data-start=\"1384\" data-end=\"1402\">in addition to</strong> federal requirements. For questions, contact HR or consult the full California Labor Code.</p>",
